			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Ever since we published the ARM instruction decoder, we've had two separate decoder tables.

native_client/src/third_party/arm-isa/armv7.table is the master copy.  We're hesitant to claim copyright on it, because it's substantially similar to the ARM ISA documentation (though since it's a mechanical description it's not clear that copyright applies, but whatever).  This used to be in private_tools, which is why we have the other copy:

native_client/src/trusted/validator_arm/armv7-opt.table is an optimized (reduced) version of the master.  Essentially, I modified the decoder-generator to write its intermediate results after optimization.

This optimization should be done as part of the build process.  Now that the master is in our public repo, there's no problem with doing it that way, and it would really simplify things.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-08-24T16:00:15.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-06-17T21:36:16.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Obsolete</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
